03:26.080 --> 03:30.687
And so all series long, we haven't just wanted to explain what the words of Psalm 23 mean.

03:31.868 --> 03:36.274
We want to experience the power and promise as a reality in our lives.

03:36.962 --> 03:41.288
A book that we've recommended all series long is by Dallas Willard called Life Without Lack.

03:41.308 --> 03:43.532
It's all about living into the fullness of Psalm 23.

03:43.892 --> 03:57.853
And he says that if we want to not just understand this in our minds, but experience the real sufficiency of our shepherd, then we need to be growing in faith or trust, in humility and love.

03:57.873 --> 04:01.638
This is what he calls the triangle of sufficiency, a slide you guys have seen.

04:02.560 --> 04:04.082
Often God allows

04:04.418 --> 04:14.770
Circumstances and situations in our lives that feel out of our control to emerge because that enables us to trust God and to learn to need Him more.

04:15.370 --> 04:19.815
