05:56.747 --> 06:01.712
I want to prove it by how well I preach and how sacrificially I serve and give and whatever.

06:03.174 --> 06:10.802
But a big invitation of Psalm 23, and this is what I hope you walk away remembering today is simply this.

06:10.882 --> 06:12.944
the shepherd love you.

06:14.266 --> 06:22.234
To really experience the fullness of life without lack and the presence of the shepherd, would you let him love you?

06:22.935 --> 06:27.740
We're going to spend the bulk of our time looking at maybe why we struggle to let the shepherd love us.

06:27.780 --> 06:40.274
But if we want to really love others, be a part of God's mission in this world, I think the thing that's missing most in Christian's lives that I talked to, it was missing in my life for a long time, was feeling like I

06:40.514 --> 06:47.784
didn't have to prove myself my worth to God, but just to simply let him love me.

06:48.845 --> 06:50.648
God really does love you.

06:51.248 --> 06:53.091
Will you let him love you here today?

06:53.672 --> 06:59.680
So I want to just share Psalm 23, the whole psalm for a final time here in our series.

06:59.840 --> 07:05.087
And if you're open and available and willing, would you please stand as we hear the very word of God.

07:05.107 --> 07:07.410
I was going to recite it from

07:07.874 --> 07:13.282
