22:23.852 --> 22:24.853
There's quality time.

22:25.194 --> 22:27.317
Help me out here for those who've read it here.

22:27.337 --> 22:27.658
What else?

22:27.678 --> 22:37.453
Quality time, acts of service, gifts, words of affirmation, physical touch.

22:37.754 --> 22:40.498
I'm not surprised you said and you ever thought of that one, Chris, huh?

22:40.994 --> 22:44.141
Anyone else physical touch for the receive love that way?

22:44.902 --> 22:45.965
I got to hug you more, Joe.

22:46.045 --> 22:47.728
I didn't realize that.

22:48.851 --> 22:59.794
Yeah, my daughter I'm learning is a huge physical touch person and it's terrifying me about what her teenage years might just be like.

23:00.215 --> 23:01.458
And we finally

23:01.570 --> 23:04.073
Her brothers couldn't handle her love language.

23:04.213 --> 23:08.519
She was constantly touching, so we finally invested in a third row vehicle.

23:08.799 --> 23:14.867
And as long as she can't touch anybody else, the ride has gotten so much better.

23:16.690 --> 23:18.392
What do you think God's love language is?

23:24.239 --> 23:28.064
I'm going to say it's maybe a sixth.

23:28.084 --> 23:29.266
I think it's obedience.

23:30.018 --> 23:38.311
In John 14, verse 15, Jesus says, if you love me, you'll obey my commandments.

23:40.755 --> 23:42.077
I think that's how we love God.

23:42.657 --> 23:49.969
We trust Him enough to believe that He really loves us, really knows us, really has our best interest in mind.

23:49.989 --> 23:56.579
So His commandments are not heavy burdens to keep us from life, but Jesus says, I have come as the good shepherd.

23:56.599 --> 23:58.642
I've laid down my life for you.

23:58.978 --> 24:01.842
so that you might have life and have it to the full.

24:01.903 --> 24:05.909
Have it abundantly, John chapter 10, verse 10.

24:07.952 --> 24:11.317
This week is John, one of our elders here alluded to.

24:11.357 --> 24:18.989
This is Thanksgiving's coming up and it's a great week to obey some of God's commands related to giving thanks and gratitude.

24:19.069 --> 24:24.658
And Colossians chapter three, Paul really emphasizes the importance of this and he writes,

24:24.866 --> 24:31.115
In verse 15, let the peace of Christ rule in your hearts, since as members of one body, you were called to peace.

24:31.756 --> 24:32.377
And be what?

24:33.178 --> 24:33.699
Thankful.

24:34.280 --> 24:44.535
Let the message of Christ, while among you richly as you teach and admonish one another with all wisdom through Psalms, hymns, and songs from the Spirit, singing to God with what in your hearts?

24:45.316 --> 24:46.017
Gratitude.

24:46.618 --> 24:54.450
And whatever you do, whether in word or deed, do it all in the name of the Lord Jesus.

24:54.882 --> 24:58.587
giving thanks to God the Father through Him.

25:00.410 --> 25:01.131
Be thankful.

25:02.032 --> 25:03.474
Have gratitude in your hearts.

25:04.335 --> 25:06.077
Give thanks to God.

25:07.519 --> 25:17.753
As I've studied about the importance of gratitude, there are different Christian thinkers throughout the centuries who would say that sin is essentially a failure of gratitude.

25:19.055 --> 25:21.138
Why do we not obey God?

25:22.786 --> 25:28.454
It could be because of a lack of gratitude that we fail to see the wondered, behold the beauty of God.

25:28.495 --> 25:32.420
We fail to see how his goodness and mercy follows us all the days of our lives.

25:32.440 --> 25:39.972
And so we think we need to go do something on our own to get what we think we really need when actually everything we ever need is really right there with God.

25:40.813 --> 25:52.210
Sin is a failure of gratitude and a radical antidote to that then to live life to the full, to obey and love God is to become people who are too grateful.

25:52.962 --> 25:53.462
to sin.

25:54.243 --> 25:58.487
Too grateful to even be tempted to want something other than what God would want for you.

25:58.527 --> 26:02.291
Imagine what that would be like.

26:02.311 --> 26:09.277
A really popular author these days is Ann Vosskamp, and she wrote a book probably a decade or so ago now called A Thousand Gifts.

26:09.938 --> 26:22.770
And in A Thousand Gifts, she makes the recommendation that if you would give thanks for three unique gifts that God's given to you each and every day, over a year's time, you would give

26:23.010 --> 26:27.395
thanks to recognize and praise God for over a thousand gifts.

26:28.257 --> 26:39.370
And studies have shown that the more thankful you are, the more content you will be, the lower your anxiety and worry will be, and the more joy you will have.

26:40.332 --> 26:46.920
Studies that are not Christian show that what God commands us to do actually really works is actually really good for us.

26:47.641 --> 26:48.722
One more reason that

26:49.154 --> 26:53.138
We should trust God and love Him by obeying His commands.

26:54.119 --> 26:59.305
So right now, I know your grandmamas will probably ask you, what are you thankful for here on Thursday?

26:59.826 --> 27:08.755
But really, what's one gift that God has given to you that you can just thank Him for right now?

27:09.596 --> 27:14.742
What's one way, His goodness, His mercy really has been following after you?

27:17.925 --> 27:18.866
Give them thanks.

27:20.258 --> 27:21.680
Recognize that.

27:22.561 --> 27:22.941
See it.

27:24.763 --> 27:26.645
And that will deepen your connection to Him.

27:29.028 --> 27:33.713
So we love God by receiving, first, the grow and love we receive God's love for us.

27:33.813 --> 27:38.378
We love God, and I think the primary way we can do that is by loving Him, obeying His commandments.

27:38.398 --> 27:40.921
And then third, we love others.

27:42.623 --> 27:46.107
In life without lack, Dallas Willard gives this definition of love.

27:46.247 --> 27:47.749
It's very profound.

27:47.769 --> 27:48.850
He says, love

27:49.570 --> 27:51.453
is to will the good of others.

27:52.374 --> 27:56.940
We love something or someone when we promote, it's good for its own sake.

27:58.021 --> 28:03.489
Love is the genuine inner readiness to secure the good of others.

28:04.590 --> 28:10.438
Love is not action, it is the source of action.

28:11.880 --> 28:16.626
See, a lot of times we can do loving things from unloving motivations, right?

28:16.802 --> 28:22.268
We can maybe do something for somebody so then it seems loving, but then they will owe us or we can control them.

28:22.328 --> 28:34.561
But we wanna become people who are so pervaded with this hessid love of God that from the natural overflow of our lives, we would just have an inner disposition to pursue the good of others.

28:35.562 --> 28:39.046
And that can be complex and we could do a long, long series trying to get into that.

28:39.086 --> 28:42.510
Sometimes we think loving others is just people policing, just doing what they want.

28:42.590 --> 28:46.674
But if people are doing things that are not good, do we wanna just

28:47.426 --> 28:52.813
Applaud them for doing that and enable them to keep doing things that's not good for them or hurtful to them, not at all, no.

28:53.414 --> 28:55.116
We sometimes have to challenge and correct.

28:55.597 --> 29:08.635
But if our disposition is really to love others, to will their good, then we will be willing to do what we need to do by God's grace to love and secure their good.

29:11.478 --> 29:17.106
I think in my own life right now is I'm kind of second half of life still

29:17.698 --> 29:45.586
41 years old here for a couple more weeks and So I look at the second half of my life I think so much for the first half of our life is trying to make it it's kind of trying to prove it trying to Show you belong that you have a place and you know what that is and second half of life I think what's lived well is not so much about me doing things as much as me helping fruits grow on other people's trees How can I not be so?

29:46.050 --> 29:58.531
focused on just what I want to accomplish, but how can I look at the lives of others and see what God might be stirring up in their lives to encourage them and equip them and help spiritual fruit grow on their trees?

29:58.571 --> 30:00.194
That's a big thing I'm thinking about.

30:00.815 --> 30:01.756
And love is difficult.

30:02.818 --> 30:09.489
Pastor John Orberg, he once said, if you want to grow spiritually, find some difficult people to help you grow.

30:10.912 --> 30:12.274
Look around the room right now.

30:15.138 --> 30:18.162
I see some difficult people that might help you grow right here.

30:18.182 --> 30:21.287
I think you're looking at one yourself.

30:21.988 --> 30:23.349
I fit in with that.

30:24.852 --> 30:35.186
But as we want to secure the good of others, we will then grow into being a loving Christ-like,

30:35.298 --> 30:36.940
Psalm 23 community.

30:37.240 --> 30:40.184
And that's his last movement here that we'll wrap up with here today.

30:40.624 --> 30:46.572
We belong to and help build a community of Christ-like loving people or the church.

30:47.493 --> 30:48.554
That's God's goal.

30:49.095 --> 30:52.939
We can't experience a life without lack merely on our own.

30:53.981 --> 30:57.485
We are sheep that are all following this shepherd.

30:58.226 --> 31:05.074
And I think throughout the series, maybe you've seen some of the videos or heard stories of how some sheep, I mean, they're not only the

31:05.186 --> 31:05.807
the brightest.

31:05.827 --> 31:10.034
They're not only the wisest and I've had some of these even recently sent to me.

31:10.074 --> 31:18.287
I think Bob just sent me one over here that sheep is just in this hole and the shepherd goes to this big painstaking effort to get them out of the pit.

31:18.387 --> 31:21.192
And then as soon as he gets out of the pit, the sheep does what?

31:21.553 --> 31:22.935
Just jumps right back into it.

31:23.456 --> 31:25.399
And that's what the church is kind of comprised of.

31:25.579 --> 31:32.370
Leaders and people that we just keep making those mistakes and we need to stay with one another.

31:32.450 --> 31:39.679
to be in community, to practice that steadfast, hased love toward one another.

31:40.920 --> 31:53.075
It's a couple nights ago, I had to hang out with some friends that I've been friends with for over 14 years and the whole time I've been here in New England and we're going around the room and just kind of catching up and sharing about our lives.

31:54.878 --> 31:58.482
And as everyone was sharing, I realized something pretty significant.

32:00.765 --> 32:01.746
Every one of those

32:02.082 --> 32:11.931
guys has hurt me in some way over 14 years, and I have let down, disappointed, and hurt each one of those guys.

32:13.853 --> 32:20.520
And yet, we haven't given up our friendship, our commitment, our relationship to one another.

32:21.741 --> 32:31.250
I think one of the things that we get really wrong about being the church is to think it's going to be perfect, and everybody's going to be behaving the way they should, when they should,

32:31.778 --> 32:40.656
And if we have that over-inflated expectation, then we're going to just grow in resentment because every single one of us here is a sinner.

32:40.717 --> 32:47.250
I would say you're a beloved sinner, not just a wretched sinner, a beloved sinner, and you have limits.

32:48.066 --> 32:50.849
Boy, that's the one thing I feel more than anything else.

32:50.909 --> 32:56.675
I feel like I let down somebody every single day because I can't be, you know, another campus.

32:56.755 --> 33:00.719
I can be one place at one time or I have other responsibilities.

33:00.739 --> 33:02.962
And I can't say all the yeses I'd like to say.

33:03.002 --> 33:05.985
And so we will let down, we will hurt.

33:06.766 --> 33:14.674
But if we've been loved with a never stopping, never giving up, unbreaking, always and forever, hessed love,

33:15.682 --> 33:17.984
And we receive that and experience that.

33:18.645 --> 33:22.529
And we can extend that and share that and promote that.

33:22.729 --> 33:38.606
And as we do, could you imagine what it would be like to be a Psalm 23 church where people are feeling and finding hope and healing and belonging in community and the sufficiency of a shepherd in a world that tells us we're not enough?

33:39.807 --> 33:42.610
So I'd like to close here today just by praying

33:43.234 --> 33:51.943
Psalm 23 over us collectively, that we would be this kind of community for the sake of the world.

33:53.064 --> 33:59.450
I believe we would be an unstoppable force by God, for good, empowered by the Spirit.

33:59.490 --> 34:00.111
Let me pray.

34:00.151 --> 34:06.958
God, thank you, thank you, thank you, that you are our shepherd.

34:08.539 --> 34:11.122
And that in you, we genuinely lack

34:11.330 --> 34:15.116
Nothing that we really need at all.

34:16.759 --> 34:23.030
Help us not just to know that as an idea in our heads, but experience that reality and the deepest parts of our souls today.

34:23.971 --> 34:31.264
Thank you for all the ways you have led us to green pastures and lead us besides still waters.

34:31.344 --> 34:37.394
Thank you for how you restore our souls and how you are maybe even doing that right now.

34:38.146 --> 34:46.015
Thank you that you lead us on right past, often past, we never could have picked for ourselves, not for our sake, but for your name's sake.

34:47.416 --> 35:02.994
I thank you, God, that even though we walk through valleys of shadows of death each and every day, that we do not need to be gripped by the fear of the enemy, we do not need to be held under the dominion

35:03.554 --> 35:08.740
of a scarcity mentality because you are with us, God, really here with us.

35:09.241 --> 35:11.964
Your rod, your staff, they protect us.

35:12.505 --> 35:13.987
So may we trust in you.

35:14.027 --> 35:20.555
Thank you, God, that somehow even in the presence of enemies, you prepare a table before us.

35:20.595 --> 35:21.336
That's abundant.

35:21.376 --> 35:24.840
So abundant that we could actually invite our enemies to come to the table.

35:26.282 --> 35:30.407
You can make restoration out of those broken situations, God.

35:31.068 --> 35:32.530
You can reconcile them.

35:33.090 --> 35:35.533
Thank you, God, that you anoint our heads with oil.

35:36.615 --> 35:42.182
You anoint us and bless us with abundance of blessing and spiritual gifts, God.

35:42.863 --> 35:45.647
And so help our lives to overflow.

35:46.428 --> 35:56.081
And thank you, thank you, thank you, Lord, that surely we can count on it every day of our lives, not some of them.

35:56.141 --> 35:59.465
Your goodness and your hassid follows us.

36:00.767 --> 36:02.930
And thank you for the hope that we have.

36:03.426 --> 36:12.377
in the face of the darkness, in the midst of despair, that one day we will forever dwell in your house.

36:14.440 --> 36:20.287
So come Lord Jesus come, thank you for being the ultimate shepherd who lays down your life for us.

36:21.628 --> 36:28.997
May we receive your love like never before and share it so that everyone everywhere would know you.

36:29.458 --> 36:32.722
We pray this all in Jesus' mighty name and everyone said together,

36:33.058 --> 36:52.530
Amen.

